bio.experienceSummary: With 8 years of hands-on experience in child caregiving, I bring a wealth of knowledge and a deep love for nurturing children at every stage of their development. Over the years, I have had the privilege of working with numerous families, building lasting relationships and becoming a trusted part of their lives. My experience spans all ages, from infants to preteens, and I take great pride in creating a warm, engaging, and secure environment for each child in my care. My genuine dedication for the children I work with drives my commitment to their growth and happiness. I understand the importance of finding someone who truly cares, and I am devoted to providing not just quality care, but also a loving presence that parents can rely on.

description.displayText:
I recommend Amanda as she was an awesome babysitter to my children. She watched my kids twice a week over the summer and it was a joy to have her. 
Amanda always came to our home on time, cheerful and ready to engage with the children. She is intelligent, kind and a great listener. My kids love Amanda, and would always look forward to spending time with her. That said, she always followed our directions in regards to the children (bedtimes, food, etc.) and they respect her as an authority figure. We still engage her services about two evenings per month. 
By hiring Amanda, you can be assured that you won't get a teenager who lounges around watching TV while your kids fend for themselves. Amanda is fun and hardworking, any family that hires her has very fortunate children.

bio.experienceSummary:
Hello Families,
 
My name is Miss Maya and I hold vast experience with children ranging in age, of both neurotypical and neuro divergent backgrounds in nannying and school-like settings! I truly value the trust it takes to put your child in the hands of someone else's care and always aim to build reliable and strong relationships with the families I support. As a nanny and educator, encouraging a healthy imagination, creativity and fostering whole-child development are my top priorities. I currently serve as Lead Teacher within a pre-school classroom, assisting toddler-aged children. My goal, is to bring these skills to your family and become an asset to your child's development. I am CPR, First Aid, AED, MAT and SCIP trained / certified as well. Thank you for your time and consideration.

description.originalText: Moved out of New york two years ago, but every time I come up north to visit I always reach out to Maya watch my three year old daughter.  She is just such a loving and caring person. Warm  and kind individual and is always punctual. I always appreciated the fact that she always keeps me updated - via text - with my daughter while I’m away. It’s nice to know what’s going on. She always makes me feel at ease, and ALWAYS has activities for my daughter to do  which is a plus. This is why I ALWAYS call Maya. She is extremely reliable and helpful!

bio.experienceSummary: With over a decade of dedicated experience working with children aged 0-18, my passion for creating nurturing environments and supporting young learners' development has grown immensely. Beyond teaching American Sign Language and admissions leadership, I have also been deeply involved in nannying roles, providing personalized care and guidance to young ones. Currently serving as an Assistant Head of School at Guidepost Montessori, I continue to expand my understanding of child development and the importance of fostering a safe and enriching educational atmosphere. I remain committed to educational equity and the holistic growth of children and am eager to explore further opportunities in the world of nannying and childcare.

description.originalText: Coley was great! She came on time and I could tell my daughter really liked her. As a new time mom, I truly felt comfortable leaving my 3 month old with her. Definitely will book her again in the future.

bio.experienceSummary:
CPR/AED Certified 
Child Development Certified. 
Choking hazards trained. 
I am 34 years old, mother of two myself. I am a loving caring woman whom adores children of all ages. very compassionate, attentive, and nurturing. Love to do activities, one on one time, park etc. provide my full attention to your child and their own personal needs and wants. I prefer to keep children occupied to minimize screen-time desires. Infant experience and knowledge of feeding (bottle/spoon fed-stages) diaper changing, sleep schedules, bottle cleansing and disinfecting, tummy time etc. offer light housework duties, laundry & food preparation. Very gentle hands with catering to newborns and all of their needs as I am a mother myself. I am kind and trustworthy. Offer child care services of all ages, and can promise that your child will always be safe and comforted with me at all times.

I have extensive child care experience. I have been babysitting for over 10 years for family and close friends. Also, I took safe sitting classes and became certified in safe sitting and CPR for all age groups. I enjoy working with children and look forward to finding work with a great family. 

I DO work a FT job so I am currently looking for something here and there or evenings.

bio.experienceSummary:
I'm a nurturing childcare provider with 15 years of experience fostering children's growth and development. I am passionate about creating a safe and nurturing environment where children can learn, play, and thrive. I believe in open communication with parents and will provide regular updates on your child's day. I am comfortable enforcing household rules and have experience caring for children of all ages from infants to preteens.

As a creative and imaginative individual, I enjoy playing both outdoor and board games with children. My skills as a swimmer have also allowed me to teach swimming to children who are interested in learning.

I have a college degree and am fluent in both English and Russian. I am also CPR and First Aid certified. I have a car and am comfortable with pets.

I look forward to the opportunity to discuss my qualifications further and to learn more about your family's needs.

I'm a dedicated childcare provider with over 7 years of experience. My passion lies in nurturing children's growth and development. I strive to provide a safe, nurturing, and stimulating environment for your little ones. I'm known for my patience, creativity, and friendly nature, making me an approachable caregiver for both children and parents.

I believe in open and honest communication with parents. I provide regular updates on your child's day, whether it's through verbal communication at pickup, text messages, or phone calls. I respect the parents' preferred communication method and follow their lead when it comes to enforcing household rules. My favorite activities to engage in with children are educational games that foster learning. I am currently located in Union, NJ. I am a full time stay at home mom to my 10-month-old daughter. I am looking to work with local working families who need childcare services while they are away at work.

description.originalText: Erinma is amazing! She is intelligent, kind, patient and so so caring. Our family hired Erinma for part-time afterschool pickup and care. She is responsible, communicative, and thoughtful with our kiddo. Erinma has made a positive impact on our home and we are grateful to know her!
